{
  "page": "Sky",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sky_waycastle_(AGoT_Comic).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/32/Sky_waycastle_%28AGoT_Comic%29.jpg/200px-Sky_waycastle_%28AGoT_Comic%29.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"351\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/3/32/Sky_waycastle_%28AGoT_Comic%29.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sky_waycastle_(AGoT_Comic).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mya Stone and Catelyn Stark arrive at Sky by Tommy Patterson for <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones_(comics)\" title=\"A Game of Thrones (comics)\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> comic</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Sky</b> is the third waycastle defending the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>, seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a>, and is the last line of the castle's defense following the <a href=\"/index.php/Gates_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Gates of the Moon\">Gates of the Moon</a> and the waycastles <a href=\"/index.php/Stone\" title=\"Stone\">Stone</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Snow_(waycastle)\" title=\"Snow (waycastle)\">Snow</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Sky is a high, crescent-shaped wall of unmortared stone raised against the side of the <a href=\"/index.php/Giant%27s_Lance\" title=\"Giant&#39;s Lance\">Giant's Lance</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> above the tree line.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Inside the walls are a series of earthen ramps and a great tumble of boulders and stones of all sizes, ready to be thrown down against attackers or even cause a minor avalanche. There is a cavern containing a long natural hall, barracks, stables for mules, and supplies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The waycastle can handle at least twenty mules.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The path to Sky from <a href=\"/index.php/Snow_(waycastle)\" title=\"Snow (waycastle)\">Snow</a> is treacherous. It is open to the wind and the steps are cracked and broken from the constant freezing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is wide enough for two to ride abreast closer to Sky, but narrows to single file closer to Sky.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>, located six hundred feet above Sky, can be reached by handholds carved in the natural rocky chimney which leads from the waycastle to the Eyrie's undercellar, or by taking wicker baskets and stout oaken supply buckets pulled by chain winches.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Sharra_Arryn\" title=\"Sharra Arryn\">Sharra Arryn</a> tripled the size of the garrisons in <a href=\"/index.php/Stone\" title=\"Stone\">Stone</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Snow_(waycastle)\" title=\"Snow (waycastle)\">Snow</a>, and Sky in preparation for the imminent march of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> forces against the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a> during <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>. Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a> evaded them, however, by flying <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>'s inner courtyard.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> stops at Sky while traveling to the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>. She is delighted to see the waycastle after traversing a high saddle between two spires of rock. Catelyn decides to take one of the baskets up to the Eyrie instead of climbing the chimney.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Horton_Redfort\" title=\"Horton Redfort\">Horton Redfort</a>, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Anya_Waynwood\" title=\"Anya Waynwood\">Anya Waynwood</a>, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Benedar_Belmore\" title=\"Benedar Belmore\">Benedar Belmore</a> choose to be drawn up to the Eyrie by the winch for Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a>'s meeting with the <a href=\"/index.php/Lords_Declarant\" title=\"Lords Declarant\">Lords Declarant</a>, while Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Yohn_Royce\" title=\"Yohn Royce\">Yohn Royce</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gilwood_Hunter\" title=\"Gilwood Hunter\">Gilwood Hunter</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Symond_Templeton\" title=\"Symond Templeton\">Symond Templeton</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Lyn_Corbray\" title=\"Lyn Corbray\">Lyn Corbray</a>, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Nestor_Royce\" title=\"Nestor Royce\">Nestor Royce</a> climb the chimney instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While descending the <a href=\"/index.php/Giant%27s_Lance\" title=\"Giant&#39;s Lance\">Giant's Lance</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Gates_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Gates of the Moon\">Gates of the Moon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Arryn\" title=\"Robert Arryn\">Robert Arryn</a> travel to Sky from the Eyrie via the wooden baskets.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The waycastle called Sky was no more than a high, crescent-shaped wall of unmortared stone raised against the side of <a href=\"/index.php/Giant%27s_Lance\" title=\"Giant&#39;s Lance\">the mountain</a>, but even the topless towers of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> could not have looked more beautiful to Catelyn Stark. Here at last the snow crown began; Sky's weathered stones were rimed with frost, and long spears of ice hung from the slopes above.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Calling this a castle is like calling a puddle on a privy floor a lake, Alayne thought, when the bucket was opened so they might emerge within the waycastle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of \"<a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Alayne Stone</a>\"</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sky&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"